article.headline: Badgers shoot 50 percent from the field
article.linkText: No. 15 Wisconsin extends home win streak to 20
article.story:
MADISON, Wis. (AP) -- Devin Harris scored 19 points and Zach
Morley added 18 to lead Wisconsin (No. 15 ESPN/USA Today, No. 18 AP) to a 75-49 victory over
College of Charleston on Saturday.

Mike Wilkinson scored 15 points for the Badgers (9-2), who shot
50 percent from the field and extended their home winning streak to
20 games.

Mike Benton scored 11 points for College of Charleston (9-2),
which had its nine-game winning streak halted.

Wisconsin closed the first half with a 21-6 run and led 36-20 at
the break. In the second half, the Badgers' lead never slipped
below 15 points.

The College of Charleston shot 26 percent in the first half and
31 percent in the game. The Cougars' top two scorers, Thomas Mobley
and Stanley Jackson, shot a combined 6-for-24 from the field and
each scored seven points.

Harris and Wilkinson combined for 17 points during Wisconsin's
decisive first-half run, which covered the final 10:18 of the
period.

College of Charleston missed 14 of 16 shots during the stretch.
